                    <msContents>
                        <summary>The fourth volume of an abridged translation of <persName
                                key="person_49372318" role="ant"><persName xml:lang="ara">ابن
                                    خلکان</persName> <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Ibn
                                    Khallikān, 1211-1282</persName></persName>'s Arabic work <title
                                xml:lang="ara" key="work_20613">وفیات الاعیان</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ara-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20613">Wafayāt
                                al-a‘yān</title>. According to the colophon (<locus from="120a"
                                to="120a">folio 120a, lines 14-15</locus>), this is an autograph
                            (i.e. penned by <persName xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc" role="trl"
                                key="person_281176268">Rodosîzade Mehmet bin Mehmet,
                                -1701</persName> himself).</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="MS_Marsh_246-item1">
                            <author key="person_49372318">
                                <persName xml:lang="ara">ابن خلکان</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Ibn Khallikān,
                                    1211-1282</persName>
                            </author>
                            <editor role="trl" key="person_281176268">
                                <persName xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Rodosîzade
                                    Mehmet bin Mehmet, -1701</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ota" type="alt">ردوسی زاده محمد بن
                                    محمد</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ota" type="alt">Rodosīzāde Meḥmed bin
                                    Meḥmed</persName>
                            </editor>
                            <title xml:lang="ota" key="work_23091">ترجمهٔ وفیات الاعیان</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23091">Tercüme-i vefeyāt
                                el-a‘yān</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="ota" otherLangs="ara">Ottoman Turkish with some
                                quotes in Arabic</textLang>
                            <listBibl>
                                <bibl>
                                    <ref
                                        target="https://menadoc.bibliothek.uni-halle.de/ssg/content/pageview/775155"
                                        >Ethé, Hermann. <title>Catalogue of the Persian, Turkish,
                                            Hindûstânî and Pushtû Manuscripts in the Bodleian
                                            Library, Part II: Turkish, Hindûstânî, Pushtû and
                                            Additional Persian Manuscripts</title>. Oxford:
                                        Clarendon Press. 1930. p. 1175 § (37) 2075</ref>
                                </bibl>
                            </listBibl>
                            <note>Translation originally prepared for <persName role="dte"
                                key="person_74645312"><persName xml:lang="ota">قره مصطفی
                                    پاشا</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="ota-Latn-x-lc">Kara Mustafa Paşa,
                                    Merzifonlu, 1634-1683</persName></persName> in <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1677"
                                        >1087 AH</date> (<date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1677"
                                            >1676/1677 CE</date>).</note>
                            <filiation>An apparently non-autograph copy of the full text of this
                                work can be found in Oxford Bodleian Libraries <ref
                                    target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_23135">MS.
                                    Sale 50</ref>.</filiation>
                        </msItem>
